# Validation: run sparingly (save time & compute)

## Do **not** run `npm run check` when

- Changes are **docs/markdown only** (`*.md`, `docs/**`, `.agents/**`), **Cursor rules** (`.cursor/rules/**`), image/assets, or copy-only edits that do not touch build tooling.
- The user’s request is **read-only** (explain, review, plan) with **no file edits**.
- You already ran `npm run check` **successfully in this session** on the **same working tree** and no further `*.ts` / `*.tsx` / `*.js` / `*.jsx` / eslint-ts config files changed since.

## Run `npm run check` **once** when

- You modified **any** of: `src/**` or `*.ts`, `*.tsx`, `*.js`, `*.jsx`, `package.json` (deps/scripts), `tsconfig*.json`, `eslint.config.*`, `vite.config.*`, or anything that affects typecheck/lint — **at the end of that coding batch**, not after every single save.

## Escalation

- **`npm run test:quick`**: only if behavior changed under test coverage and you need extra confidence.
- **`npm run verify`**: only if the user asks, or AGENTS.md full-gate triggers (release/tooling/high-risk).

## Anti-patterns

- Running check **twice** without new code edits.
- Running check after **only** bumping `package.json` version with **no** TS changes (skip).

When in doubt: **skip check** for low-risk/doc-only work; run **one** check before commit when code changed.
